#component-typography
  h4 Typography

  p.lead.
    All default HTML tags are supported, including but not limited
    to the below few examples.

  .code-sample
    pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
      &lt;!-- Add something like this to the HEAD of your page --&gt;
      &lt;!-- Will add Open-Sans(400) and Lato (300,700) as title and general font-families --&gt;
      &lt;link href="//fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,700|Open+Sans:400" rel="stylesheet"&gt;

  p For other options, check <a href="https://fonts.google.com/" target="_blank" >Google Fonts</a> out.

  .row
    .col.sm-12.md-6
      each i in [1,2,3,4,5,6]
        #{'h'+i}= 'Header ' + i

    .col.sm-12.md-6
      br

      p.
        This is an paragraph. There are <strong >bold</strong>, <i >italic</i>, 
        and <u >underlined</u> texts, also, <a href="#!">anchors</a>.

      .row
        .col.sm-12.md-6
          p 
            b Ordered lists:

          ol
            li First item
            li Second item
              ol
                li Nested first
                li Nested second ...
            li Third item

        .col.sm-12.md-6
          p 
            b Unordered lists:

          ul
            li First item
            li Second item
              ul
                li Nested first
                li Nested second ...
            li Third item

  h5 Code example

  .code-sample
    pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
      &lt;!-- Head lines --&gt;
      &lt;h1 &gt; ... &lt;/h1&gt;
      &lt;h2 &gt; ... &lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;h3 &gt; ... &lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;h4 &gt; ... &lt;/h4&gt;
      &lt;h5 &gt; ... &lt;/h5&gt;
      &lt;h6 &gt; ... &lt;/h6&gt;

      &lt;!-- Other --&gt;
      &lt;p &gt; ... &lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;b &gt; ... &lt;/b&gt;
      &lt;i &gt; ... &lt;/i&gt;
      &lt;u &gt; ... &lt;/u&gt;
      &lt;a href="." &gt; ... &lt;/a&gt;

      &lt;!-- Lists --&gt;
      &lt;!-- replace OL by UL or DL for different list types --&gt;
      &lt;ol &gt;
        &lt;li &gt; ... &lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li &gt; ... &lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li &gt; ... &lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;/ol&gt;
